<setup>
  <selectFromSequence name="c" from="1" to="2" step="1"/>
  <selectFromSequence name="k" from="0.3" to="0.6" step="0.1"/>
  <selectFromSequence name="a" from="1" to="2" step="1"/>
  <selectFromSequence name="b" from="4" to="6" step="1"/>
  
  <function name="f"> e^(-$k*x)+$c</function>
  <function name="g"> pi*(e^(-$k*x)+$c)^2</function>
  <function name="G"> pi*(-1/(2*$k)*e^(-2*$k*x) - 2*$c/$k*e^(-$k*x) + $c^2*x)</function>
  
  <math name="intValue" simplify>$$G($b)-$$G($a)</math>

</setup>  

  <p>
    Consider the function <m>f(x) = e^{-$k x} + $c</m> and the region, <m>\mathcal{R}</m>, that its graph bounds along with the <m>x</m>-axis on the interval from <m>x = $a</m> to <m>x = $b</m>.
  </p>

  <p> 
    <ol marker="a.">
      <li>
        <p>
          Sketch a graph of the region, <m>\mathcal{R}</m>, and then sketch the solid generated by revoloving this region about the <m>x</m>-axis.  
        </p>  
        <p>
          Find an integral expression that represents the volume of the resulting solid of revolution.  Do so by filling in the blanks below; once you identify the lower and upper limits of integration, those numbers will appear in the integral expression below.
        </p>

        <p>
          lower limit of integration: <m>a = </m> <answer name="lower">$a</answer>
        </p>
        <p>
          upper limit of integration: <m>b = </m> <answer name="upper">$b</answer>
        </p>

        <p>
          Integral expression for the volume, <m>V</m>, of the solid of revolution: 
        </p>
        <p>
          <m>V = \displaystyle\int_{$lower}^{$upper}</m><mathInput name="int1" minWidth="100" /><m>d</m><mathInput name="dWhat" minWidth="15"/><answer><award><when>$int1 = $g and $dWhat = x</when></award></answer> <!--, <m>$$f($h), $$g($h), $f - $g</m> -->
        </p> 
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Evaluate the integral to find the numerical value of the volume, <m>V</m>, and report the value below.  Report your result to an accuracy within <m>0.0001</m>.
        </p>
        <p>
          <m>V = </m><mathInput name="intVal" minWidth="40" /> <answer allowedErrorInNumbers="0.0001" allowedErrorIsAbsolute><award><when>$intValue=$intVal </when></award></answer>
        </p>  
      </li>
    </ol>
  </p>